Nov 26 2009 	Great Location Great Management a Little Warm Decent Food 	This hotel was picked at the last moment by a person I met on the flight from Shenzhen to Beijing. Mr. Rong could not have selected a more well rounded establishment. The Manager of the Paragon is a Canadian and his english came in more than handy. Not to mention his attention detail. When I return to Beijing, I will be staying at this HoJo. If you travel to Beijing in the summer, be prepared to be warm. Ok, down right HOT. The city government dictates the indoor temperature of all commercial establishments for energy savings. Also, be prepared to navigate on your travels without hearing the english language. Few, and I mean very few people speak english. Most taxi drivers know any english except for the occassional curse word. (funny hearing a cabby in China say FU) The hotel will give you some business cards with tourist locations written in English and Chinese so you can hand the card to the cab driver and point to the place you want to go. The card also has the hotel info on it so you can make it back. Feel free to email me any questions about: places to shop and how to bargain in Beijing.netzipper@hotmail.com	
Oct 26 2009 	Good choice at a good price.	Stayed at the Paragon for four nights in October with family (total six) in two rooms. After the most bureaucratic check-in procedure I have ever experienced we made our own way to our rooms (no bell boy service). One of the rooms had no electricity and after some 30 minutes of waiting, an engineer found the fuse box and then we were back in business. Rooms were well appointed and of a good size. Large LCD TV with limited English language channels : BBC, MTV, Bloomberg and Star Movies. Had a 'goldilocks' problem with temperature in the rooms, with one too hot and no air-con and the other too cold. Location of hotel very convenient with two underground stations in walking distance and the Beijing Railway Station directly opposite. Direct access to the Henderson shopping mall with a range of places to eat. Breakfast perfectly adequate, but only an upmarket Chinese restaurant available for dinner.Eventhough my wife is a fluent Mandarin speaker, we found the staff to be curt and disinterested, offering little in the way of tourist advice and seeming to have little knowledge of the area when asked for suggestions for places to eat.On the whole, a good choice at a good price.	
