Jun 11 2007 	Very Nice Hotel Good Location	Stayed here for 5 nights in mid-May 2007. It's a nice big, clean hotel, attached to the Henderson Shopping Complex.I think the room was one up from the &quot;standard&quot; room, but the price difference was minimal (booked through a travel agent). The room is BIG, and the bathroom is quite large (for a hotel) as well, and has a bath, and a large glass panel separating the bathroom from the main bedroom (You do have blinds you can draw closed for privacy if you want)Room included things like slippers, bath robe, electronic safe, wardrobe, fridge, TV, and internet access (via network cable, provided in the draw). I found the room was always kept clean by the cleaners, and the bathroom was well maintained and cleaned as well.Breakfast was great, a large area on the 5th floor, and had a variety of hot and cold foods - There was a large range of foods to chose from, and it was well prepared and cooked , and very clean. The only bad thing (not the hotels fault) was if travelling alone - You got up to get some food... and someone else came along and stole your table !!!!! (So leave a book or jumper on the chair!)The front desk, while professional looking, was a bit difficult to deal with. I only speak English, and a little French, and had a hard time getting information... You really have to pick the right person... Took me 3 attempts to book a tour to the Great Wall as the English is really not that good.. BUT.. They to TRY, so B+ for effort, you just have to hang in there and explain things slowly, or go away and try again after the staff change shifts !Location is great - I walk heaps, so the Square and Forbidden city is walkable - Though probably 15 minute (really fast walk) to 35 minute (really slow walk). Plus some other shopping centers the other direction (but only really for keen walkers, else grab a cab)The Henderson shopping complex I didn't really spend time shopping in, but for food (dinner, lunch) , it had several places too chose from, plus a supermarket and pharmacy are located there - and the supermarkets are really cheap for drinks and snacks.I didn't use it, but the railway station is literally across the road. Just mind your wallet/purse in the crowds - Though nothing happened to me, I was warned about it.When getting a cab, the doorstaff can help - and usually pick you a reliable cab. Get a card from them (Doormen) as you get in the cab - It's bascially a card saying &quot;Please Take me to the XXX&quot; written in Chinese.... You just tick the box you want and give it to the cab driver... Makes saying where you want to go easier (plus it also says &quot;Please take me to the Howard Johnson Hotel&quot; and gives directions on the flip side... For when you want to get back!I never got ripped by a cab hailed by the staff. But on the way BACK to the hotel... Hmmmm check the price BEFORE you start the journey.A really nice hotel, big, clean, and with a good breakfast and great location. I would recommend it, and I would stay there again. Communications can be a bit on the difficult side, but if you at least know roughly what you want to do/where you want to go before you get there - It will help.	
