Jun 23 2006	Excellent Hotel!	Howard Johnson Paragon Hotel in Beijing, is located in front of a train station and in the middle of a Shopping Center. All facilities are available, internetservice, restaurants, free currency change and a lot more. Is a bargain! You can walk to the Tianamen Square or a supermarket that is in front of the hotel. Breakfast is free, and is a 5 star breakfast. Buffet with excellent food! This is a 4 star Hotel. Does not have a pool, which is a downer, but who needs it, you have so many things to see in Beijing, that you will not have time for a pool.There is a restuarant and a karaoke club in the second floor. Beautifull Chinese girls go there. Is a very fine club. You have to pay $50 to get inside. So, the clientele is excellent, with great emvironment. Front desk was good, but sometimes employees do not speak english, but, is China. Someone very fast, comes to your assistance. Do not worry. Go to the paragon. I had an excellent vacation there. Besides, Chinese people are great!Jose Fuentes	
Mar 27 2006 	Help was very nice	I had never been to China, in fact, never left the U.S.A. before, so my world traveling skills are not well honed. I ask only for nice people who try their best. Everyone at this hotel was and did! Outside rooms are nicer view wise, and watching the railroad station across the street handle 2 million people a day is but a small glimpse into the city life. On some floors the rooms have been redone and some are not and slightly worn. But who cares!! This is China! Wow! Close to bus line and taxis at the door. Everywhere and at any time you always fell safe in Beijing. Wonderful place. I loved the morning buffet. I see that some people complaint about slow service. It's a buffet for goodness sake, don't sound so Imperialistic, get up and get it yourself!	
Sep 28 2005	Loud horrible conditions with bugs rust	This is definitely the worst hotel I stayed in china, especially for the price one pays. I interestingly noticed that my friend had a much nicer room on the coprorate floor-9th floor, for a much price then ours. We were first placed on the 5th floor, a room which faced the inner courtyard. There was music playing until 11PM and then I was awoken at 6AM to the noises of breakfast buffet (clanging of the silverware, piano music, conversations). And the front desk had the audacity to say they had updgraded us to that room the night before. When confronting the front desk about this, they did not offer me a new room- they told me to come back that same day in the late afternoon to check if there are available rooms to change to. I forced the front desk representative to find a room for me- otherwise, by the time I came back from sightseeing, there may be no more rooms available. This room we were moved to had much worser condition- only saving grace was it wasn't facing the interior courtyard. However, the bathroom was horrible- rusted fixtures, insects (dead and alive) floating throughout the bathroom, a showerhead that doesn't work (no signifant jet stream). AWFUL condition. I would not recommend staying at Howard Johnson Paragon.	
Aug 17 2005	Great location + Bargain	It is excellent not because it's the best hotel in the world but you really can't have much to complain. I got a package from Hong Kong including airfare and hotel and stayed there for 3 nights. The package was very cheap and I think this hotel probably doesn't charge a lot. Don't be alarmed by the name &quot;Howard Johnson.&quot; It is much better than regular Howard Johnsons in the US. The lobby looks nice, the rooms are fine. The hotel is well located with a subway stop right across from the street. The train station is also across the boulevard. It's very busy with millions of people coming in and out. I didn't detect noise from the street. It was wonderful to watch the actions and the view's great.	
Apr 8 2005	Take a chance on the Paragon!	When looking for a Beijing hotel to stay at with my husband and three kids I ran across the Paragon. I was frustrated because I couldn't find many reviews and the ones I did find weren't very sparkling. We booked directly through Howard Johnson and got a great rate for a Deluxe Suite, one room with 2 double beds (they were small but fine) and another with a couch, chairs, television desk etc. Ho Jo's policy kids under 17 stay for free in parents room. Nearly every other hotel insisted we book two rooms for our family. Since the rate was easily $150 per night cheaper, we decided to give it a try. WOW were we surprised! The room was great, super convenient with a subway station right at the hotel. It's across the street from the train station so was high entertainment to watch the people pouring out like ants starting at 0530. Breakfast buffet was varied and delicious. Most of the staff spoke English and they were happy to make our stay pleasant. There was a little gafaw when checking in, they couldn't find our reservation but more than made up for it over our lovely week's stay at the Paragon. Give the Paragon a chance...you won't be disappointed!	
Nov 4 2004	Centrally located good breakfast but slow service	The Howard Johnson Beijing hotel was actually better than most Howard Johnson hotels in the US. I liked the buffet breakfast (has a fairly rich choice both Chinese and Western items). But service is slow: it will take a while until a waiter notices you and brings you any coffee. Expedia has rated this hotel as three stars; it is probably better than three stars. The room rates (booked over the Internet) were reasonable. The staff did try to be helpful and spoke moderately good English The hotel is centrally located in Beijing, and taxi, subway and train transportation is nearby. Giving directions to a taxi when coming in from the Beijing airport can be a problem for foreigners: you must provide the phone number of the hotel and the exact hotel name and address written in Chinese to the taxi driver -- for some reason, finding this hotel invariably seems to require a phone call by the driver.	
Aug 31 2004	not impressed!	This hotel is a good example that the number of stars doesn't say much about appeal or quality, just about the formal list of facilities.Upon arrival not enough staff at reception to cope with the customers. Toilets in the lobby not too clean. Sub-standard service from the coffee lounge staff in the lobby. The rooms a bit shabby and the breakfast was not 4-star quality. Any good things? Yes, we could occupy the room at around 9am without surcharge and the hotel is very convenient for train travel. It locates opposite Beijing Zhan.In all quite dissappointing compared to for example the Capital Hotel I stayed last year. (which was even a bit cheaper)	
